abstract:
The research aims for the role and  behavior dung beetle efficiency in the second seed dispersal. The newness point is introduction of innovative  role in order to increase the effective usable forest biodiversity through dung beetle (2018-2019).   
The results of research 2018 from the Unila campus arboretum have found six species of dung beetle and one species has not been identified, with a total of 70 individuals (n=70); in the utilization block of Tahura WAR have found four species of dung beetle (n=68); 
in the Protection Block of Tahura WAR have found three species of dung beetle (n=208); the Captive Timor deer in Tahura WAR have found two species of dung beetle (n=37). The highest number of individuals dung beetle has been found in the Protection Block of Tahura WAR.
